        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Show reminder URLs in Reminders notes",
        "body": "Closes #59.\n\nKeeps writing the EventKit URL property and also mirrors a single URL line into notes so the link is visible in Reminders.app. Editing a URL replaces the prior mirrored line; clearing a URL removes it.\n\nValidated with the repository check. Live proof on macOS 27.0 (26A5368g) with Reminders full access: adding a reminder with `--url https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-proof` returned notes containing `URL: https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-proof`, and Reminders.app AppleScript read the same body. Editing to `https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-proof-v2` replaced that single URL line in both CLI JSON and Reminders.app body. `--clear-url` removed the URL field and left the authored notes as `Codex proof notes`; the disposable proof reminder was deleted afterward.",
